{
  "stem": "26111.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But after Kristallnacht, there was a new regulation that came out, along with many others, that no Jews were allowed to practice as doctors anymore.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "No lawyers were allowed to have law practices, Jewish lawyers.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Knowing, however-- I mean, with, with patients or clients, with Germans-- Aryan, as the word had been coined by that time-- non-Jewish Germans as patients or clients.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But the-- most of them were not allowed to practice, no matter what the religion of the client was, or the patient.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But they knew that even the Jews had to have some medical treatment, or they'll [LAUGHS] simply start an epidemic, which would be bad for the general population.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they needed lawyers in order to-- for obvious purposes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And once you qualified and you got into that group-- and they have a limited number, therefore, that was able to practice-- doctors, a number of doctors-- was able to practice, but only treating Jews as patients-- same with lawyers.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my father became one of those-- of those doctors.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "For 12 years, from birth until I was 12 years old.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "'24 to '36.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The purpose was that anti-Semitism had become worse and worse.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a small town-- relatively small town of 300,000-- provincial capital.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "East Prussians are well-known for a certain quality-- in the rest of Germany, even-- for a certain quality, which is hardheadedness, sort of farmers, not sophisticated at all.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were very ready, I would say, customers for the crap that, that the Nazi propaganda was feeding them.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "As a result, the, the anti-Semitic situation was somewhat worse there than in many other areas of the-- of the country.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I can't compare it with any specific regions.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was bad.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
